  , issueCommentBody =
      "This should do the trick for nginx (tested on v1.1.19 on Ubuntu 12.04). The iptables requirements are the same as @neumino has above.\r\n\r\n```\r\nserver {\r\n     listen 80;\r\n     server_name domain.com;\r\n\r\n     location /rethinkdb-admin/ {\r\n\r\n          auth_basic \"Restricted\";\r\n          auth_basic_user_file     /etc/nginx/.rethinkdb.pass;\r\n          proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8080/;\r\n          proxy_redirect off;\r\n          proxy_set_header Authorization \"\";\r\n     }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou can also set groups (ala the Apache config) with the [auth_digest](http://wiki.nginx.org/HttpAuthDigestModule) module (if you so choose). You will also want to grab `apache2utils` for the `htpasswd` utility, which nginx [can leverage](http://wiki.nginx.org/HttpAuthBasicModule) as well."
